# Getting Started

## What you'll need

If you're starting this and want to follow along, here are the tools, software, and equipment that you'll need:

1. Windows Machine
2. Oracle VirtualBox
3. Copy of Windows 11 Image
4. Copy of Kali Linux Virtual Box Image


## Steps to install Oracle VirtualBox
1. Open your preferred internet broswer and copy the following URL into your browser. (Remove the brackets before proceeding):
\
   https://www.virtualbox[.]org

2. Navigate to the Download page.
<div style="text-align: center;">
<img width="2483" height="1254" alt="image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/ce22b760-255f-48f5-bf82-4fd752ec5a8d" />
</div>

3. Select Windows Host and proceed to download it to your folder of choice.
<div style="text-align: center;">
<img width="2506" height="1211" alt="image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/dc234d17-da30-43c9-931a-866d891cce3a" />
</div>

4. Once the download has completed, run the installer. Click Next, Next, Yes, Install.

5. Once the installation has finished, you can now open VirtualBox via shortcut, the application on desktop, or type the name into the Start Menu search box.


## Steps to install Windows 11
1. Open your preferred internet broswer and copy the following URL into your browser. (Remove the brackets before proceeding):
\
   https://www.microsoft[.]com/en-us/software-download/windows11

2. Navigate to your recently installed Oracle VirtualBox and open it.

3. Click on New
<div style="text-align: center;">
<img width="649" height="125" alt="image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/df91e374-3a54-499d-aadf-47e0eb8aca17" />
</div>

4. There are multiple sections. Name and Operating System (4a), Unattended Install (4b), Hardware (4c), and Hard Disk (4d). 
4a. Enter in a name, select the folder you want to save Virtual Box's OS files to be located, and add your ISO that you installed. Ensure that the Type and Version are "Microsoft Windows" and "Windows 11", respectively. 
<div style="text-align: center;">
<img width="576" height="266" alt="image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/6d9b209a-ab1e-497c-a1a0-f68da05dc270" />
</div>
4b.  Create a username and password for the OS, and add in a Hostname. By default, there will be the username "vboxuser" and the hostname will be the same as the name you input in the name section in 4a.
<div style="text-align: center;">
<img width="585" height="337" alt="image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/f32d7f50-e910-4c95-ad45-c1762a83328e" />
</div>
Note: You may install the VirtualBox guest additions to add functionality to your VM, but it is not required.
Follow this link to learn more: https://www.makeuseof[.]com/tag/virtualbox-guest-additions-what-they-are-and-how-to-install-them/
</br>
4c. Leave the Base Memory and Processors as shown below.
<div style="text-align: center;">
<img width="574" height="155" alt="image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/8c49df86-c311-41b5-9750-61b678457ce0" />
</div>
